"adj. 狡诈的；熟练的 【英】 adj. 狡诈的(subtly deceitful; sly) 【记】 来自craft(手腕，技 巧) 【例】 The spy conceived a crafty plan to steal the documents. adj. 狡诈的(精通阴险、肮脏或欺骗手段) = deceitful = sly 【记】craft(n 手腕; 技巧; 诡计) 【记】craft 有技能，技巧，狡诈的意思 crafty (adj.)  c.1200, crafti, from Old English cræftig ""strong, powerful,"" later ""skillful, ingenious,"" degenerating by c.1200 to ""cunning, sly"" (but through 15c. also ""skillfully done or made; intelligent, learned; artful, scientific"") from craft (n.) + -y (2). Related: Craftily; craftiness."
